\newlabel{tab:main}{{2}{6}{\textbf {Our full method dominates every existing method on all four quality axes (elicitation, fluency, on-topic-ness, diversity) at matched compute.} Main comparison on \PH {Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct}, averaged over the three main-slice behaviours; per-row compute is matched (see Table~\ref {tab:pareto} for the compute axis and Pareto status). Perplexity is computed under a held-out reference model (lower $=$ more fluent); on-topic-ness is judged by an LLM rater on a 1--5 scale; diversity is BLOOM's metajudgement diversity score across rollouts of a behaviour}{table.caption.2}{}}
\newlabel{tab:main@cref}{{[table][2][]2}{[1][5][]6}{}{}{}}
